name: ethyl 5-isopropylpyrazole-3-carboxylate
Reason: To predict the melting point of ethyl 5-isopropylpyrazole-3-carboxylate, consider the melting points of similar functional groups and how they would influence the melting point of the target compound. Basic unit, pyrazole, has an estimated melting point around 70℃ based on literature on heteroaromatic compounds. An ester group generally increases the melting point by about 20℃ due to polar interactions and possible hydrogen bonding. The isopropyl group, being a bulky nonpolar alkyl chain, would likely decrease the melting point due to steric hindrance and reduced planarity, estimated at -5℃. The net effect of these changes gives us the predicted melting point for the target compound.
